Objective:

Complete onboarding and set up the development environment for Android development.

Activities:

Days 1-2: Onboarding:

Attended orientation sessions to understand the company culture and internship goals.
Introduced to team members and mentors.

Days 3-5: Environment Setup:

Installed and configured Android Studio.
Installed necessary SDKs and tools, including Java/Kotlin and Gradle.
Set up Git and created a GitHub account.
Familiarized with the Android Studio interface and basic features.

Days 6-9: Basics of Android Development:

Reviewed Android development fundamentals, such as activities, fragments, and layouts.
Completed introductory tutorials and small projects in Android Studio to build foundational skills.
